NO, COME ON, TAKE A PEN.

428
00:31:37,545 --> 00:31:39,430
WELL, JUST ONE. THANKS.

429
00:31:39,430 --> 00:31:41,349
AND I JUST LOVE
YOUR WOOD PANELING.

430
00:31:41,349 --> 00:31:42,767
IT'S VERY CLASSY.

431
00:31:43,251 --> 00:31:46,254
WOOD WARMS UP THE ROOM,
DON'T YOU THINK?
HONEY?

432
00:31:48,756 --> 00:31:50,758
CHUCK, WE'RE KIND OF
IN THE DARK HERE.

433
00:31:50,758 --> 00:31:54,262
WHAT EXACTLY
ARE WE LOOKING AT?

434
00:31:54,262 --> 00:31:58,816
I'VE BEEN UP ALL NIGHT AND
I THINK I'VE COME UP WITH
A FAIL-PROOF STRATEGY.

435
00:31:58,816 --> 00:32:02,737
PERCEPTION.
IT'S ALL ABOUT PERCEPTION.

436
00:32:02,737 --> 00:32:05,239
I MEAN, TODAY,
WITH THE MEDIA OUTLETS,

437
00:32:05,239 --> 00:32:07,742
THE INTERNET,
YOU KNOW, THE DISHES,
ALL THAT KIND OF STUFF,

438
00:32:08,242 --> 00:32:10,244
WHAT REALLY MATTERS IS
PEOPLE'S PERCEPTION.

439
00:32:10,244 --> 00:32:12,814
TAKE A LOOK AT THAT
WHOLE JONBENET AFFAIR.
YOU REMEMBER THAT?

440
00:32:12,814 --> 00:32:15,750
OH, BROTHER!
NOW THAT'S ONE LADY...

441
00:32:15,750 --> 00:32:18,186
WHO NEEDS TO HAVE
A HEART-TO-HEART
WITH HER MAKER.

442
00:32:18,186 --> 00:32:23,141
LOTS OF PEOPLE THINK
THAT PATSY RAMSEY
DID A BAD THING. WHY?

443
00:32:23,141 --> 00:32:27,462
[ Fart ]
SOMEONE CUT THE CHEESE?

444
00:32:27,462 --> 00:32:29,464
OH. THAT WAS ME.

445
00:32:29,464 --> 00:32:31,966
I'LL TELL YOU WHY.

446
00:32:31,966 --> 00:32:34,969
'CAUSE THAT WOMAN DIDN'T
HAVE THE PROPER SPIN.

447
00:32:34,969 --> 00:32:37,472
I MEAN, IF THAT WOMAN HAD
HAD BETTER HANDLING, HUH?

448
00:32:37,472 --> 00:32:40,475
I MEAN, EVEN IF SHE
SHED A TEAR OR TWO,

449
00:32:40,475 --> 00:32:42,477
I'LL TELL YOU, WE'D BE
CALLING HER A SAINT...

450
00:32:42,477 --> 00:32:45,480
AND GIVING HER
HER PICK OF
CROATIAN ORPHANS.

451
00:32:45,980 --> 00:32:47,732
OH. HE'S GOING TO HELL.

452
00:32:47,732 --> 00:32:51,135
THE PUBLIC IS GOING
TO BELIEVE ANYTHING
THAT WE TELL THEM.

453
00:32:51,602 --> 00:32:54,105
ISN'T IT GREAT? HUH?

454
00:32:54,105 --> 00:32:57,075
ISN'T THAT A SIN?

455
00:32:58,943 --> 00:33:01,879
ANYWAY, WE--
WE DIGRESS.

456
00:33:01,879 --> 00:33:04,365
THERE WE GO.
WHAT'S THIS?

457
00:33:04,365 --> 00:33:07,802
THIS IS THE STRATEGY.
YOU READ, DON'T YOU?

458
00:33:07,802 --> 00:33:09,303
THERE.

459
00:33:10,755 --> 00:33:14,258
WE ARE GONNA TELL EVERYONE
HOW MUCH ADAM AND GINGER
ARE IN LOVE.

460
00:33:14,759 --> 00:33:15,693
BUT I LOVE AMBER.

461
00:33:15,693 --> 00:33:17,178
NOT ANYMORE YOU DON'T.

462
00:33:17,178 --> 00:33:19,664
HE LOVES AMBER.
SHE'S A LOVELY GIRL.

463
00:33:20,148 --> 00:33:22,617
PEOPLE, PEOPLE,
TRUST ME, TRUST ME.

464
00:33:22,617 --> 00:33:24,118
WE FOLLOW MY GAME PLAN,

465
00:33:24,118 --> 00:33:28,639
NOTHING WILL GET IN THE WAY
OF OUR VICTORY.

466
00:33:33,828 --> 00:33:34,829
[ Amber ]
UNFORTUNATELY FOR ADAM,

467
00:33:34,829 --> 00:33:37,248
